shment improves children's positions within their families, as it encourages positive parenting techniques and discourages harmful practices.&#10;4. The voice of the child is consistent in expressing that physical punishment is harmful and demeaning. Ensuring children feel heard and valued in discussions about their wellbeing and safety can improve educational experiences and promote empathy, resilience, and emotional intelligence among their peers.">
