10;On the other hand, the children's commissioner and the equal protection network argue for simplicity in the Bill, stating that a simpler approach would make the legislation more accessible and easier to understand for the general public. They likely believe that a simpler definition would encourage more people to report instances of corporal punishment, leading to increased protection for children and better enforcement of the law.&#10;&#10;The disagreement lies in finding the right balance between clarity and simplicity to create a Bill that effectively addresses corporal punishment while also being easily understood by the public.">
