lies facing significant challenges, as well as awareness-raising campaigns to inform vulnerable children about available resources like Childline.&#10;3. Additionally, training and awareness within education settings should be prioritized to ensure that safeguarding leads have the right support and resources. Schools can also play a role in signposting parents to preventative services and potentially hosting such programs.&#10;4. To ensure successful implementation of new policies and legislation, it is essential to involve local authorities, social services, the Welsh Government, families, carers, and parents in the process. A major awareness-raising campaign can help ensure that all parties understand the changes and are on board with the new culture and value system for children.">
