s and other services like housing and education to ensure effective implementation.&#10;&#10;Regarding the thresholds for social care and the responsibility to make referrals, Alastair Birch emphasized that if a professional believes there is significant harm to a child, they are under a duty to report it to social care. He acknowledged the importance of maintaining trust while fulfilling this duty, noting that most referrals are made with parental consent and that professionals need to work together to ensure the best outcomes for children and families.">
