nment officials to ensure the successful implementation of the Bill, should it be passed.&#10;3. Sally Jenkins, representing the Association of Directors of Social Services, has had involvement in this area for over two years and welcomed the clarity that this Bill would bring, not only for children and parents but also for professionals. She recognizes that although this legislation is infrequently used, its implementation will significantly impact how they care for and nurture children in Wales, providing much-needed clarity. Local authorities have conducted some research to understand the potential impact and related costs, and further work is needed during the implementation phase.">
