e, Sally Jenkins from the Association of Directors of Social Services (ADSS) has been involved in this area for over two years. The ADSS has worked directly towards this point and acknowledges the significance of the Bill's implementation in clarifying how they care for and nurture children in Wales. Local authorities have researched the potential impact and related costs, with further work needed during the implementation phase.&#10;3. While Welsh Government has given a commitment to raise awareness about the Bill, Huw David suggests that having this awareness-raising aspect on the face of the Bill might not be necessary. However, he believes it would be helpful for ensuring families do not feel criminalized by the legislation. The costs associated with implementing the Bill will be identified and worked on collaboratively by local authorities and Welsh Government.">
