sh Government is hesitant to include such a duty in this Bill, as she thinks it would provide clarity for local authorities and front-line services on what needs to be done.&#10;2. Although Huw David acknowledges that there is a commitment from the Welsh Government to honor their commitments regarding awareness-raising campaigns and support for families during the implementation phase, he believes that having such a duty included in the Bill would make it clearer for everyone involved. However, he mentions that he is not a legislator or lawyer and therefore cannot comment on its implications.&#10;3. Sally Jenkins from the Association of Directors of Social Services (ADSS) does not think it is essential for this duty to be included in the text of the Bill. Instead, she advocates for discussions on nuancing during the implementation phase. She emphasizes the importance of simplicity and clarity to avoid further confusion.&#10;4. Lynne Neagle AM thanks Sian Gwenllian AM for her question and moves on to discuss other aspects of the meeting.">
