ed in those circumstances from family support services, for example—&#10;Speaker: Sally Jenkins&#10;Content: Or prevention.&#10;Speaker: Huw David&#10;Content: —or prevention services. So, we would not say, if we were aware, for example, that there was domestic abuse at a home, ‘There’s no role for children’s social services’, because there may be an assessment that that child may not be at immediate risk of harm, but we would obviously recognise that there are causes for concern there and we would offer that support. So, just to be clear about that. And">
